Put a large #pot{} of water with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat and bring to the boil.

Cut the @onion{1} in half through the root, peel and slice thinly into half moon slices. Remove the root from the @leek{1} and chop into ½cm slices. Remove the top and bottom from the @courgette{1}, cut lengthways into four strips. Chop each strip into three pieces.

Peel and finely chop the @garlic clove{1}. Pick the @tarragon{1}(leaves picked and stalks discarded) and roughly chop the leaves.

Cut the @British chicken breasts{2} into 2cm pieces, season with @salt{1/4%tsp} and a good grind of @black pepper{some}. Heat a large #frying pan{} over high heat until hot and add @oil{1/2%tbsp}. Add the chicken to the pan, brown on both sides and then remove from the pan.

> Tip: Do this in batches if necessary, so as to not overcrowd the pan and stew the chicken.

Reduce the heat to medium and add the chopped onion and leek. Cook for ~{2%mins} until they begin to soften. Add the courgette and garlic, then return the chicken to the pan. Pour in @water{250%ml}, bring to the boil and stir in the @chicken stock pot{1} until it has dissolved. Reduce the heat to low, half cover the pan with a #lid{} or #foil{} and leave to cook for ~{10%mins}.

> Tip: You want the stock in the pan to reduce by half as the chicken cooks, so take the lid off after 5 mins if there is too much liquid in the pan.

Pop the @rigatoni pasta{200%g} in the pot of boiling water and cook for ~{10%mins}. When cooked, drain in a #colander{} and then return to the pot off the heat. Season your rigatoni with @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{some}.

After 10 mins check if your chicken is cooked by making sure the centre is no longer pink. Pour in the @crème fraîche{1/2%pot}. Add your chopped tarragon, a squeeze of @lemon{1}(juiced) and then mix together with your drained rigatoni.

Serve in deep #bowls{} and enjoy!